&quot;The team lead asked that we have the same HP that Thanes have with their self buff... Request granted.&quot;<br>
is an incredibly poor interpretation of what was said by the TL.<br>
Read back through the report.  Thane hp weren't asked for--they were used as an example of how poorly equipped for melee combat Skalds are (ie. so poor we have to use RA's to reach even Thane hit point levels).<br>
In any case, most do not feel the 50-90 newfound hitpoints have added significantly to a Skald's RvR survivability. <br>
As far as melee is concerned, Skalds got maybe 50% of a potentially useful boost that they didn't ask for.<br>
<br>
You failed to mention the other defensive concern addressed in the snippet of the report that you quoted--Parry.  <br>
That request of better defense was actually more desired and can be put down on the list as &quot;Request Not Granted&quot;.<br>
<br>
The DD improvements are, on the whole, good for Skalds.  The problem is that they were also given to a class that didn't need them.  It makes Skalds marginally stronger compared to all but one other class, while negating its use as a general realm strength increase versus one realm.  This means Mythic: <br>
a.  Didn't think Midgard needed a boost versus Albion, but did versus Hibernia.<br>
b.  Didn't take realm power into consideration.<br>
c.  Just didn't want to hear Minstrels/Albion complain about it, so gave it to Minstrels.<br>
Only one of those reasons is a good one, imho.<br>
This reminds me of the &quot;Skalds ask for combined resistance chants, so Mythic gives them to Paladins, who didn't ask for them&quot; issue we got blindsided with many moons ago.<br>
<br>
Finally, regarding damage adds...<br>
They gave us 1/3 of what we thought we needed on this.  They still aren't stackable and I'm assuming they're still buggy (feel free to correct me on this if you're 'in the know').  What they gave us is needed range on a chant with questionable usefulness.<br>
<br>
Most of us feel like Mythic just did some minor hand-waving over the class and are afraid they will now pronounce us &quot;done&quot;.  In lieu of word from Mythic on the subject, there's no reason to believe otherwise.<br>
